  "market_context": "CL trading after a daily pullback, holding above the daily open. On the 4-hour chart, the 6 AM candle swept lows and closed above a series of down-close candles into an order block, suggesting bullish continuation rather than further downside.",
  "key_observation": "The 6 AM 4H candle's sweep and closure above down-close candles validated a bullish order block; the 10 AM 4H candle then formed open-low-high-close (retracement low), and the 2 PM 4H candle completed expansion by taking out the liquidity highs.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 4H chart, identified that the 6 AM candle made an opposing run down, sweeping lows and then closing back above the down-close candles into an order block.",
    "Step 2: Treated the up-close candle into that level as a bullish order block, anticipating a continuation higher rather than another leg lower.",
    "Step 3: Anticipated the retracement low would form on the flip of a new 4H candle — specifically at 10:00 AM EST.",
    "Step 4: Confirmed 10 AM printed the low and reacted up into the order block level, completing the open-low portion of the 4H candle.",
    "Step 5: Anticipated the expansion (high and close) would be delivered on the next 4H candle flip at 2:00 PM EST.",
    "Step 6: Observed the 2 PM 4H candle drove higher and took out the resting liquidity highs, completing the open-low-high-close bullish 4H sequence."
  ],
  "outcome": "Bullish continuation played out as anticipated: 10 AM marked the 4H low, 2 PM expanded and swept the liquidity highs.",
  "lessons": "Combining 4H candle profiling with the 10 AM and 2 PM 4H candle opens lets you anticipate exactly when retracement lows form and when expansion completes, anchored to a validated order block from a prior session sweep.",
